# Ui Components (`ui-components.mdc`)

# UI Components & Screens

## Tech Stack (UI)

- **Styling:** `StyleSheet.create` — no styled-components, no tailwind
- **Typography:** `Font` from `src/UIComponents/styles/Font.tsx`
- **Spacing / DS colors:** `src/theme.ts` — see **`design-colors.mdc`**
- **Story theming:** `useStoryStylePalette` → `StoryStyleUIPalette`
- **Gradients:** `react-native-linear-gradient`
- **Images:** `CachedImage` for remote URLs; `number` for `require()`
- **Animations:** `react-native-reanimated` 3.x
- **Safe area:** `react-native-safe-area-context` (`useSafeAreaInsets`, `SafeAreaView`)
- **Dimensions:** `windowWidth` / `windowHeight` from `src/Common/Supports/window.tsx`

Quest dialog frames use separate resolvers — see `quest-feature.mdc`.

---

## Design Tokens (`src/theme.ts`)

**Colors:** бери из дизайн-системы — `DesignSystemColors` в `src/theme.ts` (`text`, `background`, `line`). Не хардкодь hex и не добавляй новые цвета в компоненты: расширяй DS в `theme.ts`, если токена нет.

- **App shell** (splash, system UI, tab bar defaults) → `DesignSystemColors.*`
- **Story UI** → `useStoryStylePalette` / `resolveStoryStylePalette` (fallback: `DEFAULT_STORY_STYLE_PALETTE`)
- **Feature-only** (нет в глобальной DS) → локальный `Feature/<Name>/colors.ts`

**Layout:** `Padding`, `Margin`, `BorderRadius`, `Spacing` — не magic numbers.

```tsx
import { DesignSystemColors, Padding, Margin, BorderRadius } from '../../theme';

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    backgroundColor: DesignSystemColors.background.primary,
    paddingHorizontal: Padding.l,
    borderRadius: BorderRadius.m,
  },
  title: {
    color: DesignSystemColors.text.main,
    ...Font.heading.s,
  },
});
```

---

## Typography (`Font`)

Three semantic groups × size scale:

- `Font.paragraph.{xxs|xs|s|m|l|xl|xxl|xxxl}` — body text
- `Font.subheading.{…}` — semibold labels, buttons
- `Font.heading.{…}` — bold titles
- `Font.thinItalic.m` — decorative quotes

Font uses **SF Pro Rounded** family names — spread into `Text` style, don't set raw `fontSize` unless frame/editor data requires it.

```tsx
import { Font } from '../../UIComponents/styles/Font.tsx';

<Text style={[Font.subheading.m, { color: palette.mainTextColor }]}>{title}</Text>
```

---

## Story-Scoped Colors

Per-story UI pulls colors from Redux `storyStyle`, not raw `DesignSystemColors`.

```tsx
import { useMemo } from 'react';
import { useStoryStylePalette } from '../../Common/hooks/useStoryStylePalette';

const palette = useStoryStylePalette(story?.storyStyle ?? null);
const paletteStyles = useMemo(
  () => createScreenPaletteStyles(palette),
  [palette],
);

<View style={[styles.container, paletteStyles.screen]}>
  <MainButton
    text="Начать"
    firstGradientColor={palette.buttonFirstGradientColor}
    secondGradientColor={palette.buttonSecondGradientColor}
    textColor={palette.buttonTextColor}
    onPress={handlePress}
  />
</View>
```

Reference: `StoriesScreen` / `MyStoriesScreen` — `create*PaletteStyles(palette)` at file bottom.

**Carousel / animated transitions:** `useStoryStylePalettes(stories.map(s => s.storyStyle))` — pass full array to Reanimated hooks (`useHomeScreenAnimation`).

**Tab bar sync:** dispatch `updateTabBarColorsFromStoryStyleThunk` when active story changes (see `HomeScreen.tsx`).

