## Component Structure

```tsx
/**
 * @file MyComponent.tsx
 * @description One-line purpose.
 */
import React from 'react';
import { View, Text, StyleSheet, ViewStyle } from 'react-native';
import { Font } from '../../UIComponents/styles/Font.tsx';
import { Margin } from '../../theme';

interface MyComponentProps {
  title: string;
  onPress: () => void;
  style?: ViewStyle;
}

export function MyComponent({ title, onPress, style }: MyComponentProps) {
  return (
    <View style={[styles.container, style]}>
      <Text style={styles.title}>{title}</Text>
    </View>
  );
}

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: { marginBottom: Margin.m },
  title: { ...Font.subheading.s },
});
```

**Conventions:**
- `interface` for props at top of file
- Named export (`export function`, not `export default`)
- `StyleSheet.create` at file bottom
- Optional `style` / `*Style` override props for layout callers
- JSDoc `@file` + `@description` on screens and shared components

---

## Screen Patterns

**Сложные экраны (несколько фаз UI):** decomposed pattern — UIModel, hook, mappers, views. Эталон и полный контракт: **`screen-ui.mdc`** (`ChapterStartScreen`).

```
Feature/<Name>/
├── screens/
│   └── <ScreenName>/          # Decomposed screen (preferred for multi-phase)
│       ├── <ScreenName>.tsx   # switch по UIModel.kind
│       ├── hooks/
│       ├── models/
│       ├── mappers/
│       ├── constants/
│       └── components/
├── components/    # Feature-shared presentational pieces
└── hooks/         # Feature-shared animation/layout hooks
```

**Плоские экраны** (`screens/FooScreen.tsx`) — допустимы для простых layout; см. ниже.

**Screens (container hook):**
- Read state via `useAppSelector`; dispatch thunks — no direct Service calls for data loading
- `useNavigation<RootStackNavigationProp>()` + `ROUTES` from `src/navigation/routes`
- Account for tab bar: `const tabBarHeight = 50 + bottom` (see `HomeScreen`)
- Extract animation orchestration to `hooks/use*Animation.ts` or `use*Transition.ts` when the screen owns shared values, classifiers, or double-buffer state — **by responsibility, not line count**

**Presentational components:** receive data/colors via props; no Redux unless it's a connected container (rare).

